Package: ggraincloud
Title: Provides Raincloud Plot Templates In ggplot2.
Version: 0.0.0.9001
Authors@R: 
    person("Bradford", "Johnson", , "bradfordljohnson21@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The ggraincloud package offers a set of customizable templates for creating raincloud
    plots using ggplot2, the popular grammar of graphics in R. Raincloud plots provide a
    visually rich representation of distributions, combining elements of boxplots,
    jittered data points, and density plots. This package streamlines the process
    of generating raincloud plots, allowing for flexible aesthetic mapping and styling
    options. Whether you're visualizing data distributions or exploring patterns,
    ggraincloud makes it easy to create informative and publication-ready graphics
    with minimal effort.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    ggforce,
    ggdist,
    gghalves
